\end{document}

In order to define the active amount of Gal4 (GAL4 free in the above Equations), we needed to describe the effect of the galactose pathway on the network dynamics. In the literature, very detailed models of the galactose pathway have been presented (17). Such paradigms can be simplified in a number of ways, but it often leads to include in the model nonmeasurable complexes concentrations. Thus, we decided to use a phenomenological approach, assuming that (A8) the protein-protein interaction between Gal80 and Gal4 can be modeled as a direct inhibition of GAL80 on the promoter of SWI5, and that the strength of such inhibition depends on the medium (strong inhibition in glucose, weak inhibition in galactose). Actually we assumed that the GAL10 promoter is activated by GAL4 and noncompetitively inhibited by GAL80. The resulting phenomenological Delay Differential Equations (DDEs) model is:
