where again the symbol ^ indicates parameters dependent on the medium. From the analysis of data, we found that the value assumed by v
3 in galactose is 9 times bigger than the one in glucose. Analogously, the value of k
4 is 9 times bigger in glucose than in galactose (see Table 1).

The last assumption was introduced to take into account time delay for the maturation of d2EYFP protein. Thus, we derived two differential equations as in (11): one for the translation of mRNA to the unfolded d2EYFP protein, and one for the folded protein d2EYFP. Letting x
1 be the tTA/d2EYFP mRNA concentration, x
2 the tTA protein concentration, x
3 the unfolded d2EYFP protein concentration, and x
4 the folded d2EYFP protein concentration, the equations describing the network become:
